% Entailment-based residual pruning + deterministic ordering
% (BETA spec section 2.5).
%
% A surviving ArithmeticConstraint c is dropped from the residual set
% iff the remaining Arithmetic hypotheses Phi \ {c} already imply c
% (so c is trivially true given Phi and would add no information).
% Duplicate constraints collapse to one. The final residual list is
% sorted by its rendered form for deterministic output.
%
% Three queries probed:
%   ?- X > 5, X > 3.       -> drop X > 3 (entailed by X > 5)
%   ?- X > 5, X > 5.       -> collapse to a single X > 5
%   ?- X > 5, X < 10, X > 6.  -> drop X > 5 (entailed by X > 6);
%                                surviving list sorted lexicographically
